years,  and  since  energy  is  now  fungible,  and  it  moves  on  a  world
market,  if  we  share  our  50  years  of  coal,  just  two  percent  increase
with  the  world,  that  shrinks  it  to  12.5  years.  That  is  not  much,  is
it?

